                             Dangerous Natives
                             -----------------

ý
    In this puzzle game, you must guide your man across the playing field,
collecting all the gems off the screen. Written by Aaron Fisher, this
puzzle is controlled entirely by the mouse, moving across the field one
square at a time. Sound easy?

    Every time you move off a square, it disappears, plus there are arrows
firing in all directions, which update to their new positions every time
you make a new move. There are 3 different skill levels to this game, and
even the easy setting is rather difficult.

    This disk is freely distributable amongst all possible means of media
transfer, as long as no more than one pound is charged.

